Key Match Events: South Africa scored 382/5 in their innings.
Bangladesh were all out for 233 in 46.4 overs.
Mustafizur Rahman was caught by Miller off Williams for 11 runs.
Pre-Game Insights: Both teams were waiting until the morning of the game to find out whether their captains would be fit to play.
South Africa aimed to secure the No. 2 spot in the points table.
Bangladesh were under pressure, having lost three games after an opening victory against Afghanistan.
South Africa had scored 300-plus every time they batted first in this World Cup.
Bangladesh's Mushfiqur Rahim was their best batter, while Shakib Al Hasan's fitness was critical for the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Wankhede Stadium on October 24, 2023.
The weather was expected to be hot with high humidity.
Bangladesh had outplayed South Africa in two of their three previous World Cup matches.
